-- Taiwan Stocks: China Airlines, EVA Air, MediaTek, Radiant Opto
-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 2012-02-06T05:50:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-06/taiwan-stocks-asustek-computer-china-airlines-eva-mediatek.html
Shares of the following companies had
 unusual  moves in  Taiwan trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index fell 0.7 percent to 7,687.98, snapping
eight days of gains.  China Airlines Ltd. (2610)  (2610 TT) gained 1.7 percent to
NT$14.65, the highest close since Nov. 8.  EVA Airways Corp. (2618) 
(2618 TT) climbed 2.9 percent, the highest close since Nov. 8.
Taiwan and  China  have started exchanging views on an open skies
pact, Economic Daily News reported, citing Minister of
Transportation and Communications Mao Chi-kuo.  MediaTek Inc. (2454)  (2454 TT) lost 2.4 percent to NT$285. January
consolidated sales dropped 31 percent from a year earlier to
NT$5.16 billion, according to a statement on its website.  Radiant Opto-electronics Corp. (6176)  (6176 TT) retreated 4.3
percent to NT$111.50, the biggest decline since Jan. 2. The
liquid-crystal display backlight component maker said January
sales fell 36 percent from a year ago to NT$197.43 million,
according to a statement filed to the  Taiwan Stock Exchange .  To contact the reporter on this story:
